      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 80: The original-message parser is triggered from the `text` binding. Because `ParsedOriginalBody` is stored only by message id and is not invalidated when `OriginalBody`, `colorUrl`, or `bubble.color` changes, the delegate can keep rendering stale HTML after theme/color changes or after the model updates the original body. This is especially visible because `parseOriginalMessage` does not include the inputs used to generate the cached value. Please either clear `parsedOriginalBody` whenever `OriginalBody`/styling inputs change, or include those inputs in the cache key/reparse condition. For example:\n```suggestion\nif (showOriginal \u0026\u0026 isPluginOverwrite) {\n    if (OriginalBody !\u003d\u003d \"\" \u0026\u0026 (ParsedOriginalBody.length \u003d\u003d\u003d 0 || ParsedOriginalBodySource !\u003d\u003d OriginalBody)) {\n        MessagesAdapter.parseOriginalMessage(Id, OriginalBody, rootDelegate.colorUrl, bubble.color);\n        return \"\";\n    }\n    return ParsedOriginalBody;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "ba987c5b3b320318431dfbed533136be64fb50c8",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
