      "writtenOn": "2026-06-25T15:42:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 411: `onOriginalMessageParsed` applies the async parse result to the currently selected conversation instead of the conversation that requested parsing. If the user switches conversations before parsing completes, the result can be dropped or written to the wrong model when another conversation contains the same message id. Pass the conversation id through the parse request/signal, or look up the owning conversation by message id rather than using `get_selectedConvUid()`.\n```suggestion\nvoid MessageParser::parseOriginalMessage(const QString\u0026 convId, const QString\u0026 messageId, ...);\nQ_SIGNAL void originalMessageParsed(const QString\u0026 convId, const QString\u0026 msgId, const QString\u0026 html);\n\nvoid MessagesAdapter::onOriginalMessageParsed(const QString\u0026 convId, const QString\u0026 messageId, const QString\u0026 parsed)\n{\n    const auto\u0026 accId \u003d lrcInstance_-\u003eget_currentAccountId();\n    auto\u0026 conversation \u003d lrcInstance_-\u003egetConversationFromConvUid(convId, accId);\n    conversation.interactions-\u003esetParsedOriginalBody(messageId, parsed);\n}\n```",
      "revId": "ba987c5b3b320318431dfbed533136be64fb50c8",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
